posts.name: Ryan zheng
posts.cooked: Hey, I was testing our pathplanner autonomous the the other day. I created a simple shoot, move straight backwards and intake note, and shoot autonomous. I’ve tested the path and the robot moves straight backwards the correct distance however when I add an event that lowers and runs the intake (we have an over the bumper intake), the robot starts spinning around randomly when reaching the end of the path. When I test the autonomous code with the robot on blocks, the wheels all seem to behave like I expect them to, moving straight backwards and stopping when reaching the end of the path. Does anyone have any suggestions for what I should check? Thanks!

What if you run the path with the intake down, but not with the code commanding it to be down? That is, the path doesn’t care about the intake whatsoever. Just put the intake down physically yourself then start the path. That’ll help narrow down whether it’s some issue with putting down the intake or if it’s an issue with running with the intake down.

posts.name: jack greer
posts.cooked: Are you able to link a GitHub or something so people can look over the code?

posts.name: Andy Gasser
posts.cooked: Try running with PathPlanner’s telemetry connected and see what it thinks the robot is doing, compared to what it’s supposed to do. This is a great debug tool to help nature it down.

posts.name: Ryan zheng
posts.cooked: Ok, I ran the path today again and it turns out the problem is due to the steer motors not being characterized. I’m not too familiar using sys id to tune so is there any way to tune the feed forward by hand? Thanks!
